<plot>In this documentary short, various Morrocan women give first person accounts of their present situation. The women range from a rural illiterate woman to a film director. All of them share their hope, lives, and problems. In NISAA, these women analyze their relationship with Islam, the government, their families and their daily lives, forming a lyrical portrait of the present day Morrocan woman.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?397564</url></doc>
